<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd0fe8919-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s503"><num value="503">§ 503.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is authorized to be appropriated, out of any money in the Treasury not otherwise appropriated, not to exceed $75,000,000 to carry out the purposes of sections 501 and 502 of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd0fe891a-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(<ref href="/us/act/1949-05-11/ch98/s3">May 11, 1949, ch. 98, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/63/66">63 Stat. 66</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
